            "id": "ae13f87a06014c1b9260e",
            "questionText": "An athlete with a mass of $!$70\\,kg$!$ performs a box jump. They jump vertically, reaching a maximum height of $!$0.75\\,m$!$ above their initial standing position. The entire upward movement, from the start of the crouch to reaching maximum height, takes $!$0.6\\,s$!$. Assume the acceleration due to gravity is $!$9.81\\,m/s^2$!$. Calculate the average power output of the athlete during this upward movement.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "3d4aa5c85cad4814ac9df",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the formula that allows you to calculate the change in gravitational potential energy using the mass, gravitational acceleration, and height increase. Choose the correct option from the ones provided.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "8af41638-67d0-4304-afe4-278a3e5c24b8"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta E_p = mgh$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta E_p = \\frac{1}{2}mv^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta E_p = mg\\Delta t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "da7c3ccd1df44bf2b1fb2",
                    "stepText": "Using the formula you selected, calculate the gravitational potential energy change by using the given values: mass = 70 kg, gravitational acceleration = 9.81 m/s\u00b2, and height = 0.75 m. What is the resulting energy (in Joules)?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "514.73"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "J",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "8af41638-67d0-4304-afe4-278a3e5c24b8"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "14678b683bcc4fb786966",
                    "stepText": "Great, now let's identify the formula that relates the work (or energy change) with the time taken to calculate power. Which of the following expressions correctly represents the average power output?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "f093a546-8db4-44fa-9763-df65c6e6db0e"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$P = \\frac{\\Delta E}{t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$P = \\Delta E \\cdot t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$P = \\frac{t}{\\Delta E}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "6c2a948b54f445a190924",
                    "stepText": "Finally, use the energy calculated in Step 2 and the time period of 0.6 s to compute the average power output. What is the value of the average power output (in Watts)?",
