        {
            "id": "9bc9eb0c73084f5a8d2aa",
            "questionText": "A high-speed train, with a total mass of $!$1.5 \\times 10^5 \\; kg$!$, approaches a station at a speed of $!$30 \\; m/s$!$. Its braking system combines mechanical friction and regenerative braking. During braking, $!$6.0 \\times 10^7 \\; J$!$ of energy is recovered and transferred back to the electrical grid. Calculate the efficiency of the train's braking system in converting its initial kinetic energy into useful recovered energy.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "ecd96f3e695f4e8ea0fba",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the relevant formula to compute the train's initial kinetic energy. Select the correct formula from the options below.",
